\end{document} necessitating the measurement of both neutral and charged current events. They discriminated between the two on the basis of event length defined as the number of scintillator planes with non-zero pulse height in an event.

CHARM II [94] was a detector designed to measure sin2θW\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
