				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}
$${\bar {\nu }_{e}}$$
\end{document} would be stored. These ions would be accelerated to the energy required to produce decay neutrinos of the required energy and then stored in a race-track shaped storage ring. The Lorentz boost produces a well focussed forward beam which would illuminate one or more detectors in line with the straight sections of the storage ring. The search for CP violation would proceed by observing νe → νμ and ν̄e→ν̄μ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
